</div><h2><a href="/index.php?title=Sleep-When-You-Are-Not-Tired&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Warnings" id="gatEditSection" class="button button52 editsection" onmouseover="button_swap(this);" onmouseout="button_unswap(this);" onclick="gatTrack(gatUser,'Edit','Edit_section');" name="gatEditSection">edit</a> <span>Warnings</span></h2>
<div id="warnings" class='article_inner editable'>
<ul>
<li>Don't stress out about falling asleep, thinking "I <i>have</i> to sleep now or else..." This creates anxiety that prevents sleep. Instead, <a href="/Be-Laid-Back" title="Be Laid Back">be laid back</a> about it: "It'd be great to sleep right now, but if I don't, no big deal. At least I'll get some rest, and have a chance to relax."</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Related_wikiHows" id="Related_wikiHows"></a></p>
</div>
